definition: an excessive burden, fill to excess so that function is impaired
details:
noun
- an excessive burden
= synonyms: overburden
- an electrical load that exceeds the available electrical power
verb
- fill to excess so that function is impaired
= synonyms: clog
- place too much a load on
= example: place too much a load on
= synonyms: overcharge, surcharge
- become overloaded
= example: become overloaded
